        info: "Prophet Muhammad (c. 570–632 CE) is regarded as the founder of Islam and is believed by Muslims to be the final prophet of God. He was born in Mecca in the Arabian Peninsula into the Quraysh tribe. Orphaned at a young age, he grew up under the care of relatives and worked as a merchant, gaining a reputation for honesty and trustworthiness. At around age 40, he is believed to have received his first revelation from God through the angel Gabriel while meditating in the cave of Hira near Mecca. These revelations continued over his lifetime and form the Quran, the holy book of Islam. Muhammad began preaching monotheism, social justice, and moral reform, which led to opposition from Meccan elites. In 622 CE, he and his followers migrated to Medina in an event known as the Hijra, marking the beginning of the Islamic calendar. In Medina, he established a growing political and religious community and later returned to Mecca, where he consolidated control peacefully. By his death in 632 CE, most of Arabia had united under Islam, laying the foundation for rapid expansion beyond the Arabian Peninsula.",
